# GX-BX8B-SPIKE-R2
# Pinned inputs for the Java browser toolchain (Bx-8b). See docs/browser-runtimes.md.
#
# THIS FILE IS PART OF THE CACHE KEY once it reaches main: pages.yml/ci.yml hash
# tools/**, so editing any pin here invalidates the vendor cache and forces a
# rebuild. One place to bump, no manual key juggling. Same shape as
# tools/dart-toolchain/pins.env and tools/arm64-toolchain/pins.env.

# THE SOURCE. konsoletyper/teavm-javac -- "Java compiler in the browser", which
# is what serves https://teavm.org/playground/compiler.wasm.
#
# NOT konsoletyper/teavm. That is the AOT compiler; its releases (0.15.0 etc)
# are Maven artifacts and contain no compiler.wasm at all. Two different
# projects by the same author. TeaVM 0.13's own release notes say the
# browser-compiler work "was done mostly outside TeaVM".
TEAVM_JAVAC_REPO=https://github.com/konsoletyper/teavm-javac.git

# WHY A SHA AND NOT A VERSION. teavm-javac publishes NO releases and NO tags.
# Its README does not name a version; it says "The latest WebAssembly module can
# be found here" and points at the maintainer's own web server. There is no
# upstream version to pin to, so a commit SHA is the only pin that exists.
#
# Resolved by round 1: master HEAD, 2026-03-21, "Update teavm version to 0.13.1
# (#19)", 58 commits. Master has not moved in four months, so this pin is not
# holding back anything -- it is recording where we are.
TEAVM_JAVAC_COMMIT=7e4a44cf521694a4e326e33850dd8aec165eb5c9

# 25, NOT the 21 the README asks for. THE README IS STALE, AND ROUND 1 BELIEVED IT.
#
# settings.gradle sets, for every Java project in the tree:
#     java.sourceCompatibility = JavaVersion.VERSION_25
#     java.targetCompatibility = JavaVersion.VERSION_25
# and :javac compiles openjdk/jdk25u source, which uses unnamed variables (_) --
# final in Java 22, preview-only in 21. On 21 the build dies at
# :javac:compileJava with "unnamed variables are a preview feature".
#
# Do NOT "fix" that with --enable-preview. The build is not asking to opt into a
# preview; it is telling us which JDK it is written against, and 25 is also what
# ci.yml already installs for the CLI Java track. The workflow asserts the
# running java matches this number before it builds anything, the way
# build-dart2js.sh refuses when the installed dart disagrees with its pin.
TEAVM_JAVAC_JDK=25

# Confirmed by round 1 rather than assumed: compiler/build.gradle ends with
#     build { dependsOn buildWasmGC, buildTeaVMClassLib, generateClassLib }
# so this one task emits all four artifacts. The two archives the README credits
# to an unnamed "special tool" are just JavaExec tasks in this repo:
#     compile-classlib-teavm.bin  <- generateClassLib     (org.teavm.javac.StdlibConverter)
#     runtime-classlib-teavm.bin  <- buildTeaVMClassLib   (org.teavm.javac.ArchiveBuilder)
#     compiler.wasm + .wasm-runtime.js <- buildWasmGC     (TeaVM plugin, modularRuntime = true)
TEAVM_JAVAC_BUILD_TASK=:compiler:build

# Determined by the pinned checkout, recorded here so it is greppable:
#   gradle.properties  jdk.revision=6c48f4ed707bf0b15f9b6098de30db8aae6fa40f
#                      -> https://github.com/openjdk/jdk25u/archive/<rev>.zip  (~201 MB)
#   TeaVM              0.13.1, from Maven (settings.gradle also lists
#                      https://teavm.org/maven/repository ahead of mavenCentral)
#   Gradle             9.1.0, via the checked-in wrapper
# Nothing here is a second pin to keep in sync -- they all follow TEAVM_JAVAC_COMMIT.
